[[Image:Pieter Burmann der Jüngere - Imagines philologorum.jpg|thumb|right|Pieter Burmann the Younger]] '''Pieter Burman''' (23 October 1713&nbsp;– 24 June 1778), also known as '''Peter''' or '''Pieter Burmann''' ({{lang-la|Petrus Burmannus}}) and distinguished from [[Pieter Burman the Elder|his uncle]] as {{nowrap|"'''the Younger'''"}} (''{{lang|la|Secundus}}'' or ''{{lang|la|Junior}}''), was a Dutch [[philology|philologist]].
{{anchor|Biography|History}}
==Life== Born at [[Amsterdam]], he was brought up by his uncle in [[university of Leiden|Leiden]], and afterwards studied [[law]] and philology under [[Carl Andreas Duker|CA Duker]] and [[Arnold von Drakenborch]] at [[Utrecht University|Utrecht]]. In 1735 he was appointed professor of eloquence and history at [[Franeker]], with which the chair of [[poetry]] was combined in 1741. In the following year he left Franeker for Amsterdam to become professor of [[history]] and philology at the Athenaeum. He was subsequently professor of poetry (1744), general librarian (1752), and inspector of the gymnasium (1753). In 1777 he retired, and died on 24 June 1778 at Santhorst, near [[Wassenaar]].<ref name="EB1911">{{EB1911|inline=1|wstitle=Burmann, Pieter "the Younger" |display=Burmann, Pieter |volume=4|page=846}}</ref>
He resembled his more famous uncle in the manner and direction of his studies, and in his violent disposition, which involved him in quarrels with contemporaries, notably Saxe and [[Christian Adolph Klotz]]. He was a man of extensive learning, and had a great talent for Latin poetry. His most valuable works are: *''Anthologia Veterum Latinorum Epigrammatum et Poematum'' (1759–1763) *''Aristophanis comoediae Novem'' (1760) *''Rhetorica''.<ref name="EB1911"/>
He completed the editions of [[Vergil]] (1767){{sfnp|Burman|1746}} and [[Claudian]] (1760), which had been left unfinished by his uncle, and commenced an edition of [[Propertius]], one of his best works, which was only half printed at the time of his death. It was completed by L. van Santen and published in 1780.<ref name="EB1911"/>
==Notes== {{reflist}}
==References== * {{citation |url=http://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/de/fs1/object/display/bsb10217446_00009.html |title=P. Virgilii Maronis Opera, cum Integris & Emendatioribus Commentariis Servii, Philargyrii, Pierii, Accedunt Fulvii Ursini, Georgii Fabricii, Francisci Nansii, Joh. Musonii, Tanaquilli Fabri, et Aliorum, ac Praecipue Nicolai Heinsii Notae Nunc Primum Editae |last=Burman |first=Pieter [Petrus Burmannus] |editor-last=Burman |editor-first=Pieter [Petrus Burmannus Junior] |authorlink=Pieter Burman the Elder |volume=[http://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/de/fs1/object/display/bsb10217443_00009.html Vols. I], [http://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/de/fs1/object/display/bsb10217444_00009.html II], [http://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/de/fs1/object/display/bsb10217445_00009.html III], & [http://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/de/fs1/object/display/bsb10217446_00009.html IV] |location=Amsterdam |publisher=Jacob Wetsten |date=1746 |language=la}}
